President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Eric L. Hirschhorn was nominated for Under Secretary of Commerce for Export Administration and head of the Bureau of Industry and Security. Gladys J. Commons was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Financial Management & Comptroller). Leslie Rowe was nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Mozambique. Cynthia Stroum was nominated for Ambassador to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg. Jeff Bleich was nominated for Ambassador to Australia. Irvin Mayfield, Jr. was nominated for Member of the National Council on the Arts. President Obama also designated Richard A. Lidinsky, Jr. as Chair of the Federal Maritime Commission. These individuals bring extensive experience and dedication to their respective fields and will serve the country in various capacities.